UPDATE public.forum_threads
SET title = 'FanRealms Game Jam #1 — $100 Prize Pool | Theme: "3 Buttons Only"',
    content = E'# FanRealms Game Jam #1\n\n**Prize Pool: $100 · Duration: 72 Hours**\n\nWelcome to the first FanRealms Game Jam. We''re kicking things off with a small challenge to get the community building together.\n\n---\n\n## Prizes\n\n| Place | Prize |\n|-------|-------|\n| 1st | $60 |\n| 2nd | $30 |\n| 3rd | $10 |\n\nPrizes paid via PayPal or Venmo.\n\n---\n\n## Theme: "3 Buttons Only"\n\nYour game must use no more than 3 input buttons/keys total. That''s the only hard rule. Any genre, any art style, any engine.\n\n---\n\n## Rules\n\n1. Game must be made during the jam period (72 hours).\n2. Solo or team (max 3 people).\n3. Any engine is allowed (Godot, Unity, Pygame, etc.).\n4. Upload your game to FanRealms and reply to this thread with your listing link.\n5. Free or pay-what-you-want pricing only — no paid entries.\n6. Pre-made assets are allowed, but the game itself must be made during the jam.\n\n---\n\n## Schedule\n\n- Start: TBA — watch this thread for the official start announcement.\n- Submissions close: 72 hours after start.\n- Winners announced: within 48 hours of submissions closing.\n\n---\n\n## Judging\n\nCommunity vote — the submission with the most replies/upvotes in this thread wins. In the event of a tie, the FanRealms team breaks it.\n\n---\n\n## How to Submit\n\n1. Build your game.\n2. Upload it to FanRealms → Marketplace → Upload Asset.\n3. Reply to this thread with your listing link and a short description.\n\n---\n\nQuestions? Reply below or email jake.yanouyang@gmail.com.\n\nGood luck.'
WHERE id = '7e40e6ad-bc74-45c2-bd99-dd81128646b4';